title: Precision reprogramming: How AI tricks cancer's toughest cells
description: Scientists at University of California San Diego have developed a new approach to destroying cancer stem cells—hard-to-find cells that help cancers spread, come back after treatment and resist therapy. The new approach, which the researchers tested in colon cancer, leveraged artificial intelligence (AI) to identify treatments that can reprogram cancer stem cells, ultimately triggering them to self-destruct.
